Analyse einzubeziehen sind. Gerade dadurch ergeben sich darauf aufbauend neue Einsichten in den Charakter der einzelnen Erzählungen, sodass sich 1Kön 11-14 als ein Sammelbecken erweist, in dem unter dem Bogen einer Geschichtskonzeption ursprünglich voneinander unabhängige Erzählungen Aufnahme gefunden haben, in denen verschiedene Aspekte politischen und religiösen Lebens kritisch diskutiert werden.  aUsing Hebrew, Greek, Syriac, and Latin textual references, this study develops a model for the origins of 1 Kings 11–14. Its methodological innovation is to consider multiple traditions and combine them in the analysis. The stories of the end of the great kingdom and the founding of the northern kingdom are shown to be a reservoir of narratives that critically address various aspects of political and religious life.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  a1 Kings.  aJeroboam.  aKings.  aNorthern Kingdom.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104213920 cprintz978311042515440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311042130940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110421309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110421309/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEB